# Join strategies & broadcast

## Spark picks from sizes + hints

- **Broadcast Hash Join** — small side ≤ 10 MB or `broadcast()` — **no shuffle** — star-schema win
- **Sort-Merge Join** — both sides large — shuffles both — big fact-to-fact
- **Shuffle Hash Join** — one side fits per partition — shuffles one side
- **Cartesian / Nested Loop** — cross joins only

## Force it — and know when not to

- `broadcast(df)` / `/*+ BROADCAST(t) */`
- < 10 MB **auto** · ≤ 100 MB **force** · 100–500 MB **test** · **> 500 MB never**
- A broadcast that doesn't fit executor memory → **OOM**
